Diagnosis. In both sexes: lateral angle of pronotum acute, not projected (
Fig. 17
). Female: mesoscutum with punctures of two sizes intermixed, lateral areas with punctures not contiguous, becoming gradually sparsely punctured centrally, and surface between punctures finely micro-reticulate (
Fig. 17
); metapostnotal carinae almost straight, uniformly spaced and not radiating, median carinae always incomplete. Male: metapostnotum as long as metanotum, carinae weakly sinuous; S 4 with a central patch of hairs.
